title: [SOLVED]820-4924 not recognising battery.
message:
Have an 820-4924 that has some liquid damage. 
X for the battery status. SDA for the battery is measuring high (5.8v or so) whereas SCL is 3.4V

Never seen that before so it makes me wonder, on another note i replaced the ISL6259 to rule that out and there was no difference. 

Im guessing the SMC's all messed up? 
Thanks

title: [SOLVED]820-4924 not recognising battery.
message: First you need to fix the 6V on SDA. Probably corrosion under the battery connector, there is no other place where anything over 3.3V is present on that line. I assume that 6V is measured without the battery plugged in.

title: [SOLVED]820-4924 not recognising battery.
message:
You were spot on.
Thanks all sorted now.
